\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dui1665702869858.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dui1665702869858.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dui1665702869858.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dui1665702869858\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Layout of Repeated Occurrences\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"dui1665702869858__layout_of_repeated_occurrences_83551\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In Form components, it is common to display multiple occurrences of an entity.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dui1665702869858__p_d24509e1_d24510e1_d24511e1\">Each entity frame has an occurrence icon (<img alt=\"Occurrence repetition icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"dui1665702869858__image_evf_tpr_rcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/occrep.png?_LANG=enus\"/>) that is displayed when the entity is selected. You can create repetitions by\n         dragging this icon, either vertically or horizontally. Every repetition has the same\n         dimensions and contains the same fields as the first drawn entity. If a parent entity is\n         repeated, its child entities are also implicitly repeated.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"dui1665702869858__fig_d24512e1_d24513e1_d24514e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Repeating Occurrences</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Diagram of layout of repeating occurrences\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/repeatingoccs.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"dui1665702869858__note_w383ab1b5b7_w384ab1b5_w385ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you are using the grid widget, you only need to draw one occurrence that\n         is the size that the grid should occupy. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"erk1665702613779.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/erk1665702613779.html\" title=\"Use the grid widget to display multiple occurrences in a tabular format.\">Using the Grid Widget</a>.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dui1665702869858__p_d24518e1_d24519e1_d24520e1\">At runtime, Uniface displays occurrences only when they are populated, or when an empty occurrence is created.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dui1665702869858__p_d24521e1_d24522e1_d24523e1\">Every component entity and field has a position expressed in terms of an x and y axis on the component canvas. Fields in repeated occurrences have an offset instead of an absolute position. This offset specifies the distance between one repetition and the next, from top to bottom. By default, offsets are bound to the width and height of component entities, so the value of the offset matches the width or height of the entity.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dui1665702869858__p_d24524e1_d24525e1_d24526e1\">In form components, it is possible to disassociate the field offset from the entity offset at runtime using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$paintedfieldproperties</span>. This makes it possible for repeating occurrences to occupy less area than the first occurrence, or even to have fields overlay each other.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hqv1665702558806.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$paintedfieldproperties</a><p>Return or set the position and size for a specific instance of a field widget in a Form.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526975\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Layout of Repeated Occurrences Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Layout of Repeated Occurrences In Form components, it is common to display multiple occurrences of an entity. Each entity frame has an occurrence icon ( ) that is displayed when the entity is selected. You can create repetitions by dragging this icon, either vertically or horizontally. Every repetition has the same dimensions and contains the same fields as the first drawn entity. If a parent entity is repeated, its child entities are also implicitly repeated. Figure 1. Repeating Occurrences Note: If you are using the grid widget, you only need to draw one occurrence that is the size that the grid should occupy. For more information, see Using the Grid Widget . At runtime, Uniface displays occurrences only when they are populated, or when an empty occurrence is created. Every component entity and field has a position expressed in terms of an x and y axis on the component canvas. Fields in repeated occurrences have an offset instead of an absolute position. This offset specifies the distance between one repetition and the next, from top to bottom. By default, offsets are bound to the width and height of component entities, so the value of the offset matches the width or height of the entity. In form components, it is possible to disassociate the field offset from the entity offset at runtime using $paintedfieldproperties . This makes it possible for repeating occurrences to occupy less area than the first occurrence, or even to have fields overlay each other. Related Links $paintedfieldproperties Return or set the position and size for a specific instance of a field widget in a Form. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}